    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400 - ADJUSTMENTS -
        HEADLIGHT ADJUSTMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>HEADLIGHT ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <para>To adjust the headlight direction, release hood latch and tilt hood forward.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate adjustment control stem on rear of headlight housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900339">Item 2, Figure 39</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the adjustment screw clockwise or counter-clockwise to adjust the height of the
                headlight beam.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0900339" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900339.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 39. Headlight Adjustment</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT HARNESS</callout1>
                <callout1>2. ADJUSTMENT SCREW</callout1>
                <callout1>3. BULB / SOCKET COVER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
